-- Roethlisberger Says He Won't Appeal Commissioner's Suspension for Conduct
-- Aaron Kuriloff
-- 2010-04-26T18:32:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/roethlisberger-says-he-won-t-appeal-commissioner-s-suspension-for-conduct.html

          
          
             Pittsburgh Steelers quarterback Ben
Roethlisberger said in a statement that he would not appeal the
six-game National Football League suspension he received after
being accused of sexual assault. He was not charged with any
crime.  
